  • Subject: Marlink Ticket [1768060] - Linda Oldendorff - Sealink Service

    • Good Day Master, We received alert that your VSAT are offline. At the moment we have no remote access to your vessel. Please power off the VSAT ACU and Newtec modem for 20 minutes and then power them back on. After that please provide us with the following information: 1) Exact GPS and heading. 2) ACU mode, searching, or tracking? If tracking please indicate the satellite. 3) ACU error/notification? Press Ok to get the notification. 4) Modem LED status (RX, TX - Green/Amber/Unlit/Blinking at what rate/Steady) 5) Weather and sea condition at the vessel's location. 6) In port or sailing? If in port, any structure like building or crane blocking the antenna? Thank you sir and awaiting for your reply.

  • Subject: Marlink Ticket [1755440] - MSC Ivana ref:***URGENT*** MSC Ivana - VSAT out of order

    • Dear Master @ MSC Ivana, Kindly help to restart the XChange unit as below if you able to access the XChange terminal: Restart XChange URA Service: Please log into https://xchange-box.com and then: 1. Go to Box Settings -> System -> Power control -> Restart 2. After few minutes XChange will be rebooted 3. After XChange is available, please log into https://xchange-box.com. Enable Iridium/FBB/MSS backup at "Box Settings" so Xchange can access temporary data. 5. Go to Box Settings -> Network => Make sure "Universal Remote Access" is "On" and then please click on curved arrow 6. This should restart Universal Remote Access and we should be able to reach your good vessel. OR press the On/Off button in front of XChange terminal one time and monitor if this step able to reboot the XChange terminal. Thank you and Awaiting for your reply sir.

    • Dear Master, If there is any laptop available on your vessel, you can connect it to Port4 of HP switch (HP Procurve 1820G-8) and to access Newtec modem and VSAT ACU. You can configure the the IP address of laptop as follows. a) Click on windows key + R key on the keyboard at the same time. b) Type ncpa.cpl in the box, and then press OK. c) Select the local area connection, right click it and select Properties d) Select Internet Protocol Version 4(TCP/IPv4), double click it or click Properties. e) Now, select the “Use the Following IP address and enter the following details: IP address: 10.224.166.174 Subnet Mask : 255.255.255.240 Default Gateway: 10.224.166.161 Preferred DNS Server: 10.224.166.161 Alternate DNS Server: 8.8.8.8 If you able to have any mobile 4g connection, you may share to this laptop so we can remote in for further troubleshoot by Teamviewer or Anydesk. Thank you and awaiting for your reply.
